Sergio Garcia won the Masters Tournament in a playoff, taking his first major 18 years after he burst on the scene as a teen prodigy.
column3: Masters 2017: Sergio Garca Wins First Major Title

column2: He and Justin Rose put on a fine display of down-the-stretch, clutch golf. I was sorry some of the other scenarios didn't play out (Speith, Fowler, Couples, etc.), but there can only be one winner. I was rooting for Rose most of the day, as I haven't been a big Garcia fan, but when he hit the stick on 15 and then holed the eagle put, I started thinking better of him.   Both of them played classy golf. A pleasure to watch.
I'm happy for him - such a talent and to finally hold it together (especially after missing the birdie putt on 18) - well done, Sergio! Espana first!
Remember 10 years ago when he spit in the cup after missing shot? I always associated him with that act but now he deserves to be applauded for great golf today.
Not a huge fan in the past, but think he's more of a grown up now, and so great to see him win. He has stuck with his Dad, and that is pretty amazing.

Normally the back 9 is a test to see who won't choke.  But Sergio's aggressive play on 14 and 15 forced Rose to step up.  It was the best golf I've seen played in a major in quite a long time.  Very exciting.

Footage showing a man being violently dragged out of his seat and down the aisle from a United Airlines flight from Chicago to Louisville has sparked outrage on social media.
column3: Why was a passenger dragged off a US flight?

column2: The more I watch this, the more I am certain I will never fly this airline
Overbooking was no ones fault BUT UNITED AIRLINES. That man had every right to refuse a seat he payed for in advance. What is happening to humanity?

I usually travel a couple times a month on United. To drag a paying customer off the plane to make room for United employees is beyond unacceptable. I doubt I will ever use them again. Absolutely disgusting. That could have been any one of us.

Why were the 4 overbooked passengers let onto the airplane in the first place?  Also, a smart lawyer will sue the airline for millions simply due to the psychological trauma  inflicted upon the removed passenger. If I were an ambulance chasing lawyer I would make the same argument for the people who witnessed the event in the surrounding area. #boycotUnited (boycott is written with double t)
BOYCOTT UNITED AIRLINES for their dishonest and unethical practices against customers...and promoting violence against customers!!  Shame on the Chicago Department of Aviation!!

The flight wasn't overbooked. They had crew that were displaced and in order to get them to their correct location they asked passengers to give up their flights to allow the crew to travel. When no one offered to give up their seats on that plane, they randomly chose people to forcibly remove from the flight. Outrageous airline behaviour.
I wonder whether that security officer would have been suspended or the CEO of United would have been so "upset" if this event hadn't been caught on video...

This passenger was a medical doctor. When they asked him to leave, he refused it because he had to see his patients next day. United will pay big time about this savage action. Never fly with United again!!

This should not be allowed.  These policemen should be incarcerated and dismissed.  There is no excuse for such brutality!  He should sue the whole police Department, the Airport authorities and United Airlines!
I just don't know.  What's the punishment for selling things you don't have?  Airlines need to stop overbooking, and this wouldn't even be an issue.

Am I missing something here? Why is everyone arguing over whether or not it was right to have to remove passengers? Surely the question is why on earth was he removed in this way?? From what I've read, the man is a doctor and needed to be on the flight to see his patients. No one volunteered to give up their place so they chose 4 people at random and he refused. Yes I agree we don't know in what way he refused and he may have been very rude but that still gives these men NO right to drag and humiliate him like this.

Another reason to avoid traveling to Trump's America. Bullying and brutality seem to be the order of the day. With the exception of a couple of people vocally protesting, hardly a passenger flinches. 'Good German' syndrome. Way to go, U.S.A.
He was being evicted from his paid seat to enable four United employees to fly.  Not an idiot.

It shows you where United's priorities lies.  It's more important to transport their employees than a a doctor who has to get to his destination so that he can help his patients.  He should sue United.

If you read the second part bbc posted it clearly has the airline saying the that they volunteered that man too leave and he refused since he is a doctor and had to be at a hospital in the morning. The airlines statement then states that they called law enforcement to forcibly remove him. Hope he gets millions

Hello.....this is America.  We are supposed to be civilized.  Smash his face in and remove him?????  Drag him?????  Are we kidding here?  United did this to us in November.  They actually suggested that my partner and I take separate flights for our big 3 day vacation, the next day, whittling it down to 2.  Uh no.  Then charged us for ski boots coming back when they didn't charge us going in.  They are terrible.  Just a huge reason to NEVER fly them again.

The only reason someone should be forcefully removed from a flight is if they've violated the rules in some way and refused to leave when asked and not with so much force I've seen on another site pictures of this man bleeding out of his mouth before they dragged him out of that seat. That should not have happened. Not only should United be held accountable, but that whole flight crew should be investigated by the FAA, and those three police officers should be suspended without pay and investigated by their department for possible excessive force. Shame on United and those officers involved.

We just had a terrible experience flying United this weekend...every flight was overbooked and two were delayed causing  us to miss our connection and be stranded.   Never again United, between this video and our experience, you lost a customer!

I think what the airlines did is terrible. Awful. But why did all the passengers just sit there and take video? Was there not one other person who would stand up and say "take me, I will fly tomorrow"? Seeing the man was so distressed to miss the flight, could not one person have done something amazing and selfless? Yes, this still falls completely on the airlines but I'd like to think people could put down the phones and stand up.
To United Airlines. After this?! I will never book a flight on your airline again. EVER! You are a disgrace. And I hope that man sues you into oblivion. Your actions were disgusting!!

Disgraceful & Shameful.  It wasn't even because of over booking. They needed to free up 4 seats for flight staff that needed transporting to another flight. Hard to believe an elderly man could be dragged down an isle like that because of the airlines own incompetence! And why did they choose him. It more than likely had something to do with him being Asian.
We watch the world burn every day, but then we see examples of how things are changing for us, and it chills us to the bone.

Why were people allowed on the plane if they had been "chosen" for bumping? Why not keep upping the offer until they had all four needed seats? I'm sure someone could have been tempted with the offer of first class seats the next day as well as an overnight hotel and meals. This man had a good reason to keep his seat...and how did he get BACK on the plane?
This is going to end up costing United Airlines millions of dollars in lost revenue plus the lawsuit. What an incredibly stupid thing for a company to do.
Shame on you, united! I will never fly this airline! This could be me next time. I hope this guy sues the hell out of you! Disgusting!
The entire airline of passengers should have stood by this guy and walked off the plane!!!!! Disgusting what the world has come to!

Story from Wiki just a cut and paste On April 9, 2017, United Airlines Flight 3411 was operated by an Embraer E170 flying from Chicago O'Hare (ORD) to Louisville (SDF). Before departure, but after passengers had boarded and were seated, United bumped four passengers to make way for four United Airlines staff members who needed to get to a connection point.[1] Passengers were offered up to $800 to take a later flight, but with no volunteers, a manager boarded and selected four people to leave the flight. One of the four passengers selected for removal refused to leave. United Airlines staff requested assistance from police officers from the Chicago Department of Aviation. In the ensuing scuffle, the passenger suffered injuries to his head and mouth, and was taken to hospital with non-life threatening injuries.[2]  Background	  The later flight offered by United Airlines was scheduled for the next day at 3 p.m., while this overbooked service was on a Sunday night. The loss of an entire working day might have contributed to the lack of uptake of the offer. Furthermore, the passenger that refused to leave, and was injured, claimed to be a physician with patients he needed to see.[3]  Aftermath	  United C.E.O. Oscar Munoz tweeted: This is an upsetting event to all of us here at United. I apologize for having to re-accommodate these customers. Our team is moving with a sense of urgency to work with the authorities and conduct our own detailed review of what happened. We are also reaching out to this passenger to talk directly to him and further address and resolve this situation.[4] In a letter to employee, however, Munoz defended the crew's actions and claimed the passenger was "disruptive and belligerent".[5] One of the officers who removed and dragged the passenger was placed on administrative leave pending review. The Chicago Department of Aviation said that The incident on United flight 3411 was not in accordance with our standard operating procedure and the actions of the aviation security officer are obviously not condoned by the Department...[2]

United said they did a random selection which is contrary to DOT and UA's own policies. I don't know why the media didn't bother to check with UA or the DOT website...RULE 25 DENIED BOARDING COMPENSATION Denied Boarding (U.S.A./Canadian Flight Origin) - When there is an Oversold UA flight that originates in the U.S.A. or Canada, the following provisions apply: Request for Volunteers UA will request Passengers who are willing to relinquish their confirmed reserved space in exchange for compensation in an amount determined by UA (including but not limited to check or an electronic travel certificate). The travel certificate will be valid only for travel on UA or designated Codeshare partners for one year from the date of issue and will have no refund value. If a Passenger is asked to volunteer, UA will not later deny boarding to that Passenger involuntarily unless that Passenger was informed at the time he was asked to volunteer that there was a possibility of being denied boarding involuntarily and of the amount of compensation to which he/she would have been entitled in that event. The request for volunteers and the selection of such person to be denied space will be in a manner determined solely by UA. Boarding Priorities - If a flight is Oversold, no one may be denied boarding against his/her will until UA or other carrier personnel first ask for volunteers who will give up their reservations willingly in exchange for compensation as determined by UA. If there are not enough volunteers, other Passengers may be denied boarding involuntarily in accordance with UAs boarding priority: Passengers who are Qualified Individuals with Disabilities, unaccompanied minors under the age of 18 years, or minors between the ages of 5 to 15 years who use the unaccompanied minor service, will be the last to be involuntarily denied boarding if it is determined by UA that such denial would constitute a hardship. The priority of all other confirmed passengers may be determined based on a passengers fare class, itinerary, status of frequent flyer program membership, and the time in which the passenger presents him/herself for check-in without advanced seat assignment....no mention of a random selection here.

A 2008 United States Geological Survey estimates that areas north of the Arctic Circle have 90 billion barrels of undiscovered, technically recoverable oil (and 44 billion barrels of natural gas liquids ) in 25 geologically defined areas thought to have potential for petroleum. This represents 13% of the undiscovered oil in the world. Of the estimated totals, more than half of the undiscovered oil resources are estimated to occur in just three geologic provinces  Arctic Alaska, the Amerasian Basin, and the East Greenland Rift Basins.[1][2][3] More than 70% of the mean undiscovered oil resources is estimated to occur in five provinces: Arctic Alaska, Amerasia Basin, East Greenland Rift Basins, East Barents Basins, and West GreenlandEast Canada. It is further estimated that approximately 84% of the undiscovered oil and gas occurs offshore. The USGS did not consider economic factors such as the effects of permanent sea ice or oceanic water depth in its assessment of undiscovered oil and gas resources. This assessment is lower than a 2000 survey, which had included lands south of the arctic circle.[1][2][3]A recent study carried out by Wood Mackenzie on the Arctic potential comments that the likely remaining reserves will be 75% natural gas and 25% oil[citation needed]. It highlights four basins that are likely to be the focus of the petroleum industry in the upcoming years: the Kronprins Christian Basin, which is likely to have large reserves, the southwest Greenland basin, due to its proximity to markets, and the more oil-prone basins of Laptev and Baffin Bay. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petroleum_exploration_in_the_Arctic

PYD's Moslem calls on the Coalition to declare Rojava no-fly zone PYD Co-president Saleh Moslem called on the coalition forces to declare Rojava airspace a no-fly zone in order for the elimination of threats by Turkey, saying We are fighting both ISIS and Turkey at the same time.   ANF - AL GLER  BRUSSELS  Sunday, 30 Apr 2017, 11:56 73 Turkish state's recent aerial attacks on YPG and YB positions and civilian areas in Rojava and Shengal, which came as YPG-led SDF continues its operations against ISIS in Rojava and Syria at full force, caused reactions.  Rojava's Democratic Union Party (Partiya Yekitya Demokrat, PYD) Co-president Saleh Moslem who also reacted against the attacks pointed out that Turkey carried out such attacks to give a breathing space to ISIS whenever it is left desperate in the battle with Kurdish forces.  We cannot fight on two fronts at the same time. This would put us under a strain. Coalition forces should declare Rojava airspace a no-fly zone in order for the elimination of threats by Turkey, said Moslem who also criticized international powers for not manifesting a strong reaction against Turkey.  PYD Co-president Saleh Moslem answered ANF's questions about Turkey's attacks on Rojava and Shengal, the approach of international powers and current subjects on the agenda.  "TURKEY ATTACKS US WHENEVER ISIS REMAINS DESPERATE"  Turkey has launched several ground attacks on Rojava so far. Yet, the recent airstrike was the first one of its kind. How should this be evaluated? Is a new process underway?  It grabs attention that this recent attack of the Turks came after the referendum, through which he (Erdoan) seeks to portray himself as a sultan. To this end, he shows his power by carrying out such an attack. This airstrike came after Turkey's repeated ground attacks that targeted Efrn and surroundings at the border. It goes without doubt that these targets had been determined beforehand. Qereox is known to be the headquarters of YPG. The same thing also goes for Shengal. The hitting of peshmergas in particular is a message to the Kurds because it was a deliberate attack meant to intimidate the Kurds. It gives this message to international powers, the U.S. and Russia in the first place: "I will destroy the Kurds". This is an old plan of theirs anyway. When looked at the timing of Turkey's attacks, it is seen that Turkey attacks us every time ISIS gets trapped and remains desperate. This attack came while Tabqa is about to fall."  You act with the International Coalition in Rojava and Syria. Significant advances have been made especially in the Raqqa operation. What is the reaction of these parties in the face of such an attack? There has been no serious reaction as much as was reflected in the press. Did you have a private conversation with them?  Turkey acts disingenuously. Short before the attack, it said both Russia and the U.S. that "PKK is there, I will strike them", which gives no respond opportunity to the other side. This latest attack was also conducted this way. Neither Russia nor the U.S. accepted it. There are things that are not reflected in the press. To the extend I know, the US Ambassador to Ankara also reacted against the attack. US commanders made inspections at the scene and voiced reactions. Yet, this reaction is not at the level we desire. Following this attack, people demand the declaration of Rojava a no-fly zone. If this is not done, Erdoan's attacks will continue.  "ISIS ON ONE SIDE AND TURKEY ON THE OTHER"  What is it you want?  We demand a no-fly zone and we want Turkey to retreat from Rojava and Syria entirely. We do not want Turkey to intervene the region at all because of the fact that it has plans on the region and seeks to create a conflict. We want Turkey to keep its hands off Syria.  SDF and YPG made some statements that they could halt the Raqqa operation in the event that Turkey's attacks continue. Is there such a subject on the agenda?  There is ISIS on one side, and Turkey on the other. As a matter of fact, both sides are ISIS. Should such attacks continue, the situation will get hard at both fronts. YPG will then have to defend the people as they cannot fight ISIS by leaving the people to the mercy of Turkey. Our burden will be heavy.  What are your relations with the US and Russia like at the moment?  Our relations are within the framework of the deals we made before. In military terms, they are acting with the SDF. We are fighting terror with Russia in and around Efrn. Our agreements remain in effect. Both the US and Russia are against these policies of Turkey. They may remain silent due to some accounts but they are disturbed by Turkey's attacks and no side is pleased with Turkey's acts. Still, we do not trust any side. We will mount our defense ourselves.  Will Turkey's attacks be responded by your side?  Definitely, the attacks will not go unanswered. Our people are resisting, although not in the form of a regular army. Our people will resist just like they resisted in the process of Koban battle. The attacks conducted by Turkey two days ago were responded.  There is almost no country left in the Middle East and even the world with which Turkey did not have problems. All sides are disturbed by Turkey. However, the KDP is acting with Turkey in this process. How would you comment this?  KDP is in the hands of Turkey, dependent on Turkey in all aspects, which is why they cannot act against it. KDP became a part of Turkey's policies on Rojava and Shengal. The Barzani family is completely basing on their familial interests and for this reason they remain in the arms of the enemy. This will make KDP lose in long term because the Kurdish people see this truth.  "GERMANY SHOULD BAN THE TURKISH FLAG"  YPG and YPJ became a symbol all around the world. However, Germany has banned their symbols. How do you evaluate this ban?  Today, all the world and European community stands with the Kurds. We have relations with these communities and their institutions, all of which show their solidarity with us. However, the situation changes when looked at the political interests of the states. The UK is selling weapons to Turkey and the same thing goes for Germany as well. They are doing such things to preserve these interests of theirs. However, we know that these symbols are raised all around the world today. If they are looking for a connection with terrorism, I believe that Germany should ban the Turkish flag first. It is Turkey that acts with terrorism, supports and harbors it. For this reason, Turkey's flag should be banned in Germany in the first place. German people are fond of YPG-YPJ flags rather than Turkey's flag. These bans are not judicial. We hope Germany will reverse this fault because it is an inconsistent and ridiculous decision. Our lawyers are dealing with this issue at the moment.  Responding to a motion submitted by German Left Party MP Ulla Jelpke, German Interior Ministry stated that "We met with neither PYD Co-chairs nor representatives so far." Did you have any meeting with German officials?  We as a party had no official meeting with them but we have an administration in Berlin, although not on behalf of the party directly. They also know this, and maintain relations in this framework. Yet, we had several meetings with German commissions, party leaders and parliamentarians up to date.

Geoengineering is the scientifically used term for artificial modification of Earths climate systems through two primary ideologies, Solar Radiation Management (SRM) and Carbon Dioxide Removal (CDR). According to the chemtrail conspiracy theory, long-lasting trails left in the sky by high-flying aircraft are chemical or biological agents deliberately sprayed for sinister purposes undisclosed to the general public. Believers in the theory argue that normal contrails dissipate relatively quickly, and contrails that do not dissipate must contain additional substances. These arguments have been dismissed by the scientific community as Conspiracy theories: such trails are normal water-based contrails that are routinely left by high-flying aircraft under certain atmospheric conditions. Although proponents have attempted to prove that the claimed chemical spraying does take place, their analyses have been flawed or based on misconceptions.  Because of the widespread popularity of the conspiracy theory, official agencies have received many inquiries from people demanding an explanation, and rarely do the authorities make attempts for Accountability to the public, citing its a conspiracy and not worth investigating. Believers in the conspiracy theory speculate that the purpose of the claimed chemical release may be solar radiation management, psychological manipulation, human population control, weather modification, or biological or chemical warfare, and that the trails are causing respiratory illnesses and other health problems.

Presented by three mathematicians - Dr Hannah Fry, Prof Norman Fenton and Prof David Spiegelhalter - it hones in on just three key numbers that clarify all the important questions around climate change. The stories behind these numbers involve an extraordinary cast of characters, almost all of whom had nothing to do with climate change, but whose work is critical to our understanding of the climate. The three numbers are: 0.85 degrees (the amount of warming the planet has undergone since 1880) 95 per cent (the degree of certainty climate scientists have that at least half the recent warming is man-made) 1 trillion tonnes (the total amount of carbon we can afford to burn - ever - in order to stay below 'dangerous levels' of climate change) Understanding how scientists came up with these three numbers gives a unique perspective on what we know about the past, present and future of our changing climate. *Daily Manna:* *********************************  MONDAY MAY 8
  *Blessed Are Those Who Wait*
 *********************************  TEXT: ISAIAH 30:18-26
 Key verse:
 *_And therefore will the LORD wait, that he may be gracious unto you, and therefore will he be exalted, that he may have mercy upon you: for the LORD is a God of judgment: blessed are all they that wait for him (Isaiah 30:18)._*
  The world is accustomed to haste. Everyone prefers to travel on the fast lane, own fast cars, fast telephony, fast Internet connections and eat fast foods. With the world wired together by awesome communication technology into one small global village, many business and lifestyle decisions can be made in no time by the touch of a gadget. The world is filled with the plague of impatience from coast to coast. Sadly, many Christians have contracted this syndrome and have been stung by the haste bug.
  God warned Israel about rebellion and lack of patience in waiting on Him. He informed them that in quietness and in confidence will their strength be after their repentance. He therefore promised to be gracious and merciful to them, if they will wait for Him.
  Waiting on the Lord, however, should not be assumed to mean stoppage of all efforts towards the realisation of ones set goals. Being patient for God to intervene in our affairs does not turn us into fatalistic believers, doing nothing and hoping for something. Waiting for God actually means turning to Him in prayers, trusting in His word for the things we desire, doing our best as may be required and looking up to Him, until He sends the blessings we ask for.
  Whatever the needs of our lives  child-bearing, marriage partner, marital bliss, good job, healing, personal spiritual growth, ministerial progress  waiting is an activity that involves the pursuit of God for the realisation of desires. Whoever waits on God must earnestly seek His face and stand upon His promises until the requests are granted. For our waiting to be fruitful therefore, it has to be accompanied by holiness and blamelessness, faith, courage, hope, patience and service unto the Lord.
 *********************************  *THOUGHT FOR THE DAY:* An impatient Christian is like a vehicle without brakes.
  The Bible IN ONE YEAR: 2 CHRONICLES 1-4
 *********************************  *Please slow down!!*  Good morning
